value.0: Dangerous predators of the northern reaches, winter wolves pursue their prey relentlessly. Their breath is said to be cold enough to shatter stones. It watches you with a preternatural intelligence, but does not appear to be aggressive... at the moment.

While obviously advanced in age, this crone seems spry and healthy. Her skin looks like old, weathered leather and her hair as long since lost all of its color, but her body is deceptively toned beneath the wrinkles and drenched, frost-stiffened robes. She moves as though she is just as physically capable as when she was in her prime, standing in a bitterly cold rushing stream, and fishing with strikes of her bare hand.

This man's extremities are discolored by some prior instance of frostbite. Some of his digits are missing, but those that remain are hooked into savage talons, and he seems just as capable of enduring whatever pain they may still cause him, as sharing that pain with others.

Clad in pure white robes, the Grandmaster of the Frozen Hand is neither tall nor muscled, but his unblinking icy stare promises a painful death to any who show him a mote of disrespect. He clutches a solid iron staff mottled by a thin layer of rime in his gnarled claws, seemingly ready to shatter those who succumb to his gelid powers.

A shock of short black hair and a swarthy complexion immediately set this athletic, lithe figure apart from the others in the hall. Pale blue eyes that steam with a white mist leap out in stark contrast to his body's earthy tones. Like the rest of the Frozen Hand this ascetic is garbed in sheer white, though his cloth is a smart tunic and leggings rather than a more traditional robe.
A small, entirely localized phenomena whips up the snow and ice around it in a perpetually whirling, blistering cold vortex. The smell of conifers is strangely strong in the freezing wind.
These are the tracks of some large mammal that passed through the stream, leaving icy impression of its paws behind in the snow.
